CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley...Left center: Another section of the banquet room...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Women, including one wearing plaid dress, and men, seated in wooden folding chairs around table, in Central Baptist Church for banquet honoring Rev. Talley
